</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB2FFE4D0BCFD1F7A88FD3F" blockId="12.[151,1437,641,1311]" box="[151,640,641,668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB2FFE4D0BCFD1F78E5FD3F" bold="true" box="[151,237,641,667]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Length</emphasis>
(including forewing): 
<specimenCount id="11E1FD22FFB2FFE4D1C0FD1F7A08FD3F" box="[491,512,641,667]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="C01F9B4EFFB2FFE4D22CFD1F7A74FD3F" box="[519,636,641,667]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.097" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="10.97">10.97 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB2FFE4D0ECFD3B79EDFC31" blockId="12.[151,1437,641,1311]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB2FFE4D0ECFD3B79C4FD1B" bold="true" box="[199,460,677,703]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body dark brown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB2FFE4D289FD3B7AF3FD1B" box="[674,763,677,703]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,185,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[169,1417,174,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. A–E, Balala karenia Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂:A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view. F–J, Balala mekongiaTang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂: F. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; G. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; H. Habitus, dorsal view; I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635598/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Crown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB2FFE4D342FD3B7BB6FD1B" box="[873,958,677,703]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,185,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[169,1417,174,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. A–E, Balala karenia Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂:A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view. F–J, Balala mekongiaTang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂: F. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; G. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; H. Habitus, dorsal view; I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635598/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
) anterior margin round, length shorter than 1/2 width between eyes. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB2FFE4D3A5FD567C03FD47" box="[910,1035,712,739]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,185,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[169,1417,174,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. A–E, Balala karenia Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂:A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view. F–J, Balala mekongiaTang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂: F. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; G. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; H. Habitus, dorsal view; I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635598/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Figs. 9B, E</figureCitation>
) approaching or even reaching apex of clavus, exposed part of mesonotum about 1/8–1/6 scutellum length, scutellum with centre moderately swollen and slowly declining toward apex, median longitudinal ridge very strong and extended entire length of scutellum. Forewing with one transparent band present between apical cells and appendix. Abdomen with pair of continuous yellow patches mainly on 5th and 6th tergites submedially. Hind femur with 5 macrosetae, tibia with ca. 10, 10 setae in rows AD, PD, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB2FFE4D0ECFC017D6DFBC8" blockId="12.[151,1437,641,1311]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB2FFE4D0ECFC017971FC1D" bold="true" box="[199,377,926,953]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB2FFE4D1C1FC017A4BFC1D" box="[490,579,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[196,1388,194,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[188,1399,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Balala karenia Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂: A, B. Pygofer, dorsal view; C. Pygofer, ventral view; D, E. Subgenital plate, ventral view; F. Aedeagus, dorsal view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, dorsal view; H. Aedeagus, lateral view; I. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635600/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Figs. 10</figureCitation>
A–E) with dorsal inner margin slightly wavy and a slightly serrate, subapex of ventral margin with pair of indistinct teeth, few small short setae arranged along ventral margin; ventral appendage tapering and nearly reaching apex and curved dorsad, with one small tooth at subapex. Subgenital plate shorter than pygofer side. Apical margin of connective (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB2FFE4D286FB947B0EFB80" box="[685,774,1034,1060]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[196,1388,194,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[188,1399,174,1913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Balala karenia Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. Holotype ♂: A, B. Pygofer, dorsal view; C. Pygofer, ventral view; D, E. Subgenital plate, ventral view; F. Aedeagus, dorsal view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, dorsal view; H. Aedeagus, lateral view; I. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635600/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Figs. 10</figureCitation>
F–I) slightly wavy; style about 1.2x longer than connective; aedeagus shaft tubular with pair of slender processes at apex, pair of small horn-like processes present dorsally on basal part submedially, preatrium broad and about as long as shaft, gonopore between processes at shaft apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
