<subSubSection id="4FFD6520FFB2FFE4D0ECFB2378DCFABB" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB2FFE4D0ECFB2378DCFABB" blockId="12.[151,1437,641,1311]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB2FFE4D0ECFB237933FB73" bold="true" box="[199,315,1213,1239]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB2FFE4D39AFB237BF4FB73" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1907" box="[945,1020,1213,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB2FFE4D39AFB237BF4FB73" box="[945,1020,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Balala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the distinct male genitalia including 1) pygofer ventral appendage with one small preapical tooth and 2) aedeagal shaft with slender furculae at apex.
</paragraph>
